  • Method Details

    • getGame

      public Game getGame()
      Retrieves the game instance associated with this ClientModel.
      Returns:
      the current game instance, or null if no game is set.

    • getNickname

      public String getNickname()
      Retrieves the nickname used by the client for the game
      Returns:
      the nickname as a String, or null if no nickname is set.

    • setGame

      public void setGame(Game game, String nickname)
      Sets the current game for the client model. This method also notifies the view of a game update event.
      Parameters:
      game - the game instance to be set.
      nickname - the nickname of the player associated with the game.

    • getLogs

      public List<String> getLogs()
      Retrieves the list of logs maintained by the client model.
      Returns:
      a list of strings representing the logs.

    • addLog

      public void addLog(List<String> newLogs)
      Adds a list of log messages to the client's log history. Maintains a maximum of 10 log entries by removing the oldest log when the limit is exceeded. Notifies listeners of log updates.
      Parameters:
      newLogs - a list of new log messages to be added

    • displayJoinableGames

      public void displayJoinableGames(List<Game.GameInfo> infos)
      Notifies listeners with a list of joinable games available. The method triggers a property change event named "JOINABLE_GAMES", passing the provided list of game information.
      Parameters:
      infos - a list of Game.GameInfo objects containing details of joinable games.

    • setListener

      public void setListener(PropertyChangeListener listener)
      Sets the listener that will handle property change events for this object.
      Parameters:
      listener - the PropertyChangeListener to be notified of property changes.
